ients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--2"><article id="node-253906" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/sugar"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/sugar.jpg?itok=5jpB1ol9" width="100" height="100" alt="Sugar" title="Refined sugar is the most popular type of sweetener and it is made from sugar cane or sugar beet" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/sugar">Sugar</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">shuh-ga</span><p>Honey and syrups made from concentrated fruit juice were the earliest known sweeteners. Today,â€¦</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="700ml semi-skimmed milk">700ml semi-skimmed <a href="/glossary/milk" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--3 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">milk</a><span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--3"><article id="node-260691" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/milk"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/milk-resized.jpg?itok=z-tC0wLi" width="100" height="100" alt="" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/milk">Milk</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">mill-k</span><p>One of the most widely used ingredients, milk is often referred to as a complete food. While cowâ€¦</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="pinch grated nutmeg">pinch grated <a href="/glossary/nutmeg" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--4 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">nutmeg</a><span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--4"><article id="node-6458441" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/nutmeg"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary-item/glossary-image/2017/03/nutmeg_700.jpg?itok=tuPKYNYY" width="100" height="100" alt="Nutmeg" title="Nutmeg" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/nutmeg">Nutmeg</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">nut-meg</span><p><span style="line-height:107%">One of the most useful of spices for both sweet and savoury</span>â€¦</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="1 bay leaf, or strip lemon zest">1 bay leaf, or strip lemon zest</li></ul></div></div> </section> <section id="recipe-method" class="responsive-tabs__pane"><h2 class="responsive-tabs__pane-title">Method</h2><div class="method"><ol class="method__list"><li class="method__item" itemprop="recipeInstructions"><p>Heat oven to 150C/fan 130C/gas 2. Wash the rice and drain well. Butter an 850ml heatproof baking dish, then tip in the rice and sugar and stir through the milk. Sprinkle the nutmeg over and top with the bay leaf or lemon zest. Cook for 2 hrs or until the pudding wobbles ever so slightly when shaken.</p></li></ol></div> <footer class="recipe-info"><div class="recipe-info__publication">Recipe from Good Food magazine, <a href="/search/recipes/date/1141171200" class="text-style-alt">March 2006</a></div> <a class="recipe-info__magazine-ad" href=" https://www.buysubscriptions.com/print/bbc-good-food-magazine-subscription?promo=GFBS718&style=Brand&utm_medium=brandsite&utm_source=bbcgoodfood.com&utm_campaign=recipe_GFBS718_Brand&utm_content=recipe-banner" rel="extern